texts.text: >One day in the Hideout...
>A lively scene unfolds in the living room.
Oh, [sys user_name]. Hello.
Hey, Newbie...! What's with the bag? Did you go shopping or something?
>You start taking out a pile of snacks from the bag.
Autumn Kitty Kandy and special fall-edition chocolates?
Pumpkin pudding, sweet potato and mont blanc chestnut flavors...
Wow! They all look yummy!
Mont blanc? Let me see.
Hey, what the...? This is that yellow stuff...
Oh, right. Vince only eats the brown-colored ones.
Again with your weird likes and dislikes...
I splurged.
They're for everyone.
But it really is easy to get lost in the all of snacks that are sold during this time.
Wait, it's all on Newbie?! Awesome!
Yo, the packagin's all Halloween-themed. It's fall alright...
Chestnuts, pumpkins, sweet potatoes... All flavors that go with the season.
And it's all startin' to look real good for some reason...
The "season of good eats", I guess?
I'm more of a reader than an eater. I've even read a few dozen books in a single night.
A few dozen?! How...?
Fan-made books with a Halloween theme are perfect for these long, autumn nights.
Ah, those.
Jeng Yun, weren't you drawing something the other day?
Yes. It's a great season for art too! I've been making a few Halloween-themed illustrations.
Wait, really?
But what about sports? I figured you would say that and take your shirt off.
I train all year round to begin with so...
Spring, summer and winter are all a good time to take it off.
Just to prove it, I'll do it right now!
Well, if you insist...
Ririn, you're such a snake...

*Chuckle*
A sight for sore eyes.
Excuse me for interrupting, everyone. Megakin, might I have a word?
Yo, what's up?
It's for personal reasons, but I'd like to take some time off to conduct research.
The item shop will be closed for about a day while I'm gone.
Ah, got it. It ain't a problem as long as you let us know when but...
Hang on, where exactly are you goin' if you don't mind me askin'?
A bit away from the city, but not too far.
There's a harvest festival that caught my eye.
And it's just the season for it, so I thought I'd go take a look.
Would you like to join me?
A Japanese festival! In the fall and not the summer too!
Vince! I want to go!
Huh?
I want to go, but don't want to go without you, Vince.
So let's go together, partner!
Yeah, alright. Let's go...
I'll go, but don't plan on me doing much else.
Newbie, you too! Let's go!
Yeah, let's go!
She's so cute...!
Without hesitation.
Yo, lightspeed.
That's a "yes", right? Yay, we're going!
Aight, I should go out and get some fresh air too.
Gonna be tough for me... I've got work scheduled.
But our place is doing some Halloween stuff too, so I'll soak that in.
I need to work on a presentation, so I'll hold down the fort while you're away.
Alright, then I'll meet up with everyone that is going in a few days.
It is research, but I'm hoping to have some fun too.
>A few days later...
Here?
>You arrive at an eerily quiet shrine.
>The brisk autumn air adds to an already lonely atmosphere...
Yes. The locals said that they give some of their crops to this shrine as an offering.
Yo... This it?
Some potatoes, a few fruits... And flowers too.
It's... How do you put it? "Less is more..."
It's pretty sad.
Ouch.
Yeah...
I'm just calling it like I'm seeing it. Is there really even a festival?
Y'all... Yo, I tried to soften the blow.
Most of the residents are growing very old,
while less and less people are participating in this festival.
It was bothering me, but this festival may be on the verge of disappearing.
What do you mean disappearing?! There's no way I'm letting that slide!
Huh? Whoa...!
>Something rushes by everyone's feet and jumps onto the altar!
What the hell is this?!
I thought this was the time of the festival, but...
They call this an offering?!
The shrine's getting all rusty and... How'd this happen?!
A rabbit...?
Who are you calling a "rabbit"? I'm the Hare of Inaba!
Don't put me in the same boat as any boring old rabbit out there!
Yo, you're a demon? You seem pissed...
Interesting...
Hm, what's up?
I've been researching native rituals and charms for demons,
but I never thought I'd meet a demon with such a deep connection to them.
Megakin, would you mind if I tried talking to it?
I've brought along some protective equipment just in case this happened.
Doesn't look dangerous so... Yo, why not?
Hm? What was that?! You got a problem with me?!
Oh, no. Never.
My name is Kazufumi Fukumoto. I'm just an ordinary folklore researcher.
There's a few things I'd like to know about the harvest festival that takes place here...
Is there anything you can tell me?
It's not like I live around here, but yeah, I know some stuff.
It's been a while since I was last here, but I have been here before. A lot!
Buuut!
I'm not telling heathens like you anything!
Oh... I think we made it mad.
Yo, Mr. Rabbit. Help us out, won't ya?
Help you...?
You give me no respect and expect me to help you?
What do we do?
I can make it talk if you really need to hear what it knows.
Oh. In that case, if you would ever so kindly...
Leave it to Honey! It's torture time!
Whaaa?!
Whoa, stop right there. Honey, what did you just say...?
I thought torturing it would get it to spill its guts the fastest...

*Snicker*
You get an A for "Absolutely Evil"!
F-Fine! I'll talk! Then you'll stop, right?!
But I need something in return.
Offerings need to be made to the god of fertility!
This stuff hardly amounts to a meaningful offering.
Which is why you'll need to gather more.
Enough so that this festival can actually get off the ground.
In return, I'll tell you about this place and its festival!
Offerings, huh? Like what?
What?! You don't even know...
Ugh, how do you not know even that...?
This time of year... Chestnuts and beans are harvested.
And plenty of other stuff is ripe for picking too!
Oh... And dango! Perfectly round dango!
Dango... We can make those, but crops are gonna be more of a problem, yo.
Can't we just buy some?
No, that would defeat the purpose...
I know, but what other choices do we have?
Then... How about we try this?
Most of the residents here have their own fields.
But many of them are getting very old.
If we explain our situation, we may be able to help them with the harvest,
and possibly receive some of their crops in return.
Well, I guess a demon's involved so...
Yo, it ain't what we usually do, but let's give it our best shot!
